POPULAR Thobela FM producer Mpho Moraswi and his brother Lehutse will appear again in court today. He faces a charge of assualt while his brother faces two counts of murder and one of attempted murder. READ: MFR SOULS IN SCARY ACCIDENT! They were arrested after an incident at the Talenteng Entertainment Centre at Mashite Village, in GaMphahlele outside Polokwane, last Thursday. A scuffle had broken out between the Moraswis and the father of Jacky (26) and Ruben (46) Tema. The two brothers died of gunshot wounds and their father was injured. Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo said Lehutse allegedly shot the Tema brothers with his licensed firearm, instantly killing Jacky, critically wounding Ruben, and injuring their dad. Mpho, who produces the Madibogo a Gauta weekend drive show, was granted bail of R1 000 on Monday in the Lebowakgomo Magistrates Court. Lehutse was denied bail. “Ruben succumbed to his injuries in hospital on Saturday while the father is still recuperating in hospital,” Mojapelo said. He said a vehicle apparently belonging to one of the Moraswi brothers was burnt to ashes by an angry mob after the incident. READ: ZUMA VISITS CAPITEC BRANCH WITH DUDU MYENI “We’ve confiscated the firearm used during the incident and Lehutse will be subjected to an inquiry to determine if he’s fit to possess a firearm,” Mojapelo said. Provincial commissioner Lieutenant-General Nneke Ledwaba warned gun owners not to take firearms to drinking spots. Acting SABC spokeswoman Mmoni Seapolelo said the matter was being handled by the police.